  "texts": [
    "The definition of ductal morphology primarily depends on the ductal appearance of prostate cancer, and splitting a region with ductal adenocarcinoma of the prostate into patches causes the disappearance of ductal morphology in some patches.",
    "Therefore, we specifically reviewed and included only patches that represented their corresponding finding labels.",
    "The threshold was identified and set to 90% using the development set via the same approach for threshold determination for Gleason pattern detection, as described earlier.",
    "A total of 92 nonoverlapping patch images (512 × 512 pixels; ~ 512 × 512 µm at 10 × objective magnification) covering cribriform Gleason pattern 4 (n = 37) or ductal adenocarcinoma with cribriform architecture (n = 58) were obtained to simulate a cribriform pattern (Table 14).",
    "The true label of patch images was defined based on the regional delineation and its labels on histology slides made by a single pathologist, \"YT\"."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}